parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission jumping out of gear can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or crashes, especially when accelerating or decelerating.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
causing the motorcycle to jerk or jolt; the motorcycle fails to shift; the transmission slips or hesitates; the motorcycle experiences erratic behavior while in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear output shaft bearing assembly can cause vibrations while riding, which can lead to loss of control and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.

unusual noises or sounds from the rear of the motorcycle.
